Introduction
============
The ACIFIM package includes the implementation of the Adaptive Combined Incomplete Factorization and Inverse Matrix 
preconditioning technique in C++ programming language. The package also includes an implementation of the Preconditioned 
Bi-Conjugate Gradient Stabilized iterative method based on the ACIFIM scheme. Functions for reading and writing Matrix 
Market files are also provided.


Installation
============
Building the ACIFIM software is performed by the issuing the following command on the root folder:
   make

Before issuing ``make'' command in the terminal, the full Intel environment (Intel oneAPI) should be (initially installed and then) 
sourced, i.e: source /opt/intel/oneapi/setvars.sh.

External Libraries
==================
This ACIFIM package requires the following external libraries:

Intel oneAPI - This library contains optimized verions of BLAS, LAPACK and other software packages and is required by EPBiCGSTAB. The
	       library can be downloaded from https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/developer/tools/oneapi/onemkl-download.html for
               different operating systems.


Example Programs
================
The directory example/ includes an example file on how to use the ACIFIM package to solve large unsymmetric sparse linear systems.
This can be performed by navigating to the example folder and issuing the command: 

./example.out sherman2.mtx sherman2_rhs1.mtx 0.01 0.01 2 C

The example program requires 3 inputs: (1) Coefficient matrix file in Matrix Market format, (2) Right hand side vector file in 
Matrix market format, (3) Drop tolerance for LDU (\epsilon_1), (4) Drop tolerance for GD^{-1}H, (5) Number of relaxation steps (n_r)
and (6) Preconditioning mode (I,E,C).
